  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "過度正當化效應 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-overjustification-effect",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / motivation / rewards / meaning</p>\n    <h1>過度正當化效應</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Overjustification Effect</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">當一件原本願意自己做、也覺得有意義的事，被過度包裝成獎懲與外部誘因後，人可能反而更少把它當成自己想做的事。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『多給誘因就會做更多』和『誘因可能重寫人做這件事的理由』拆開，因為很多管理設計都忽略了動機來源會被改寫。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>動機心理 / 獎勵副作用</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>External rewards can undermine intrinsic motivation</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>內在動機、獎勵強度、控制感、持續性</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能更審慎地設計獎勵，不把原本健康的內在動機意外掏空</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>內在</span>\n      <span>外獎</span>\n      <span>轉移</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>獎勵能推動行為，但有時也會把『我願意做』改寫成『我只是為了拿這個』</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">過度正當化效應抓到的是動機來源被替換的風險：外部獎勵不只是加法，有時會改變整個行動解釋。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>獎勵能在短期提高產出，但若方式讓人覺得自己被控制，原本的興趣、責任感與自我驅動反而可能下降。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先分辨任務原本的動機來源</strong>\n        <p>原本就靠興趣、責任或專業認同在撐的事，最怕被粗暴量化成獎懲。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再看獎勵語意</strong>\n        <p>獎勵是在肯定成果，還是在把行為改寫成被控制的工作？</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後保留自主與意義</strong>\n        <p>外部激勵若不尊重自主，長期常會吃掉內在動機。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一件本來做得不錯、加了激勵後反而變味的工作開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">過度正當化效應在教育、社群貢獻、內部分享與創造性工作中特別值得注意。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>團隊原本自發寫內部教學筆記；後來改成每月記點排名，短期數量上升，長期內容深度與主動性卻下降。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>問題不是獎勵本身，而是獎勵把『我想做』慢慢改寫成『我為了拿分做』。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">原本有內在動機</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">外部獎勵高調進場</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">行為理由被重新解釋</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>過度正當化效應提醒你：激勵不是只會增加，也可能置換。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看誘因副作用的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">越是仰賴興趣、認同與責任感的工作，越要小心外部獎勵的語氣與強度。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>原本內在性</strong>\n        <p>這件事原本是不是有人願意自發做好？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>獎勵控制感</strong>\n        <p>它讓人覺得被肯定，還是被管理與量化？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>任務性質</strong>\n        <p>創造性、教學性與關係性工作，通常比機械任務更怕被粗暴外獎改寫。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>持續性</strong>\n        <p>當獎勵移除後，行為是否比原本更難維持？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>短期看起來像</th>\n            <th>長期可能發生什麼</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>學習與分享</td>\n            <td>數量上升</td>\n            <td>內容深度與自發性下降</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>開源貢獻</td>\n            <td>大家衝點數</td>\n            <td>動機轉成刷績效而非解問題</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>帶人與協作</td>\n            <td>活動被做出來</td>\n            <td>原本的責任感和互助感被稀釋</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼獎勵有時會把事情做壞</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為人不只在做事，也在理解自己為什麼做；一旦理由被外獎接管，內在意義就可能退後。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>理由會被重寫</strong>\n        <p>如果外部報酬太顯眼，人會更容易把行為歸因到報酬。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>控制感會被侵蝕</strong>\n        <p>越像被管理，越不容易保持自發感。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>移除獎勵後落差更大</strong>\n        <p>當外部支架抽掉，內在動機若已被吃掉，行為就更容易掉下去。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">過度正當化效應不是反獎勵，而是提醒獎勵會改寫人對自己行為的理解。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把動機保護帶回管理與學習設計</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程團隊來說，知識分享、 code quality、 mentoring 與開發者體驗這類工作，很容易因錯誤激勵而失去原本的自發性。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>知識庫貢獻</strong>\n        <p>把分享完全量化成排名，可能會養出大量低價值內容。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Code quality</strong>\n        <p>若只獎勵特定數字，工程師可能轉向對分數負責，而不是對品質負責。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>學習文化</strong>\n        <p>如果所有進修都變成被檢核任務，探索感會快速下降。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>在加獎勵前，先問這件事現在靠什麼內在動機在運作，別輕易把它換掉。</li>\n      <li>好的激勵更像支撐與肯定，不像把人變成只對分數反應的裝置。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">過度正當化效應不是說不能用獎勵，而是說獎勵會帶副作用。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>所有獎勵都不好</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。重點是任務性質、獎勵語意與是否侵蝕自主感。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只在小孩教育才有</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>成人工作、社群與專業文化同樣會被影響。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要獎勵夠大就不怕</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>很大有時反而更容易蓋過原本的意義來源。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我是在增加動力，還是在替換掉原本更健康的動力</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果把獎勵拿掉，這個行為會比現在更弱多少</strong>\n        <p>差距越大，代表你越可能在置換動機。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>這個獎勵讓人覺得被肯定，還是覺得被管理</strong>\n        <p>感受差異會直接改變長期效果。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 intrinsic motivation、self-determination theory 與 reward design。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 overjustification effect 為主，再把概念帶回管理激勵、學習文化與團隊行為。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Overjustification effect 條目整理了外部獎勵如何削弱內在動機的經典觀察。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overjustification_effect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Overjustification Effect</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>動機背景</strong>\n        <p>Intrinsic motivation 可作為對照，理解什麼樣的任務原本靠內在動機運作。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intrinsic_motivation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Intrinsic Motivation</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>理論背景</strong>\n        <p>Self-determination theory 有助於理解自主、勝任與連結感如何影響動機品質。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-determination_theory\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Self-Determination Theory</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一項你們想加激勵的行為，先問它現在靠什麼內在動機在撐，再決定要不要動。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
